    <node id="Ras" maxvalue="1">
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="SOS | SHP2"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P01116"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/20498032"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/20963626"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/23922955"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/23153558"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/20840540"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/20651362"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>&lt;Description&gt;
Ras proteins bind GDP/GTP and possess intrinsic GTPase activity. Plays an important role in the regulation of cell proliferation. Alternates between an inactive form bound to GDP and an active form bound to GTP. Activated by a guanine nucleotide-exchange factor (GEF) and inactivated by a GTPase-activating protein (GAP). Interaction with SOS1 promotes exchange of bound GDP by GTP.
&lt;/Description&gt;

&lt;HGNC&gt;
KRAS
&lt;/HGNC&gt;

&lt;Uniprot&gt;
P01116 (RASK_HUMAN)
&lt;/Uniprot&gt;

&lt;Observation&gt;
Expressed in AGS.
Known mutations in AGS.
Reported to be active in unperturbed AGS cells in 6 publications (PMID 20498032, 20963626, 23922955, 23153558, 20840540, 20651362)
&lt;/Observation&gt;</comment>
      </annotation>
