    <node id="TAK1" maxvalue="1">
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="TAB"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/O43318"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/24009751"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/16495515"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>&lt;Description&gt;
Once activated, acts as an upstream activator of the MKK/JNK signal transduction cascade and the p38 MAPK signal transduction cascade through the phosphorylation and activation of several MAP kinase kinases like MAP2K1/MEK1, MAP2K3/MKK3, MAP2K6/MKK6 and MAP2K7/MKK7. These MAP2Ks in turn activate p38 MAPKs, c-jun N-terminal kinases (JNKs) and I-kappa-B kinase complex (IKK).
&lt;/Description&gt;

&lt;HGNC&gt;
MAP3K7
&lt;/HGNC&gt;

&lt;Uniprot&gt;
O43318 (M3K7_HUMAN)
&lt;/Uniprot&gt;

&lt;Observation&gt;
Expressed in AGS.
Reported to be active in unperturbed AGS cells in 1 publication (PMID 16495515) and inactive in 1 publication (PMID 24009751).
&lt;/Observation&gt;</comment>
