        </linklist>
        <comment>&lt;Description&gt;
As their name implies, the dual-specificity phos- phatases can dephosphorylate two types of residues, threonine and tyrosine. The function of these phospha- tases is to dephosphorylate and therefore inactivate the MAP kinases (Slack et al., 2001; Liu et al., 2005a), ERKs, p38MAPKs, and JNKs. (PMID: 18922965)
&lt;/Description&gt;

