          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/22421143"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/22907434"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>&lt;Description&gt;
Complex of proteins central in regulation of cellular metabolism, growth and survival in response to hormones, growth factors, nutrients, energy and stress signals. Activated mTORC1 up-regulates protein synthesis by phosphorylating key regulators of mRNA translation and ribosome synthesis. This includes phosphorylation of EIF4EBP1 and release of its inhibition toward the elongation initiation factor 4E (eiF4E). Moreover, phosphorylates and activates RPS6KB1 and RPS6KB2 that promote protein synthesis by modulating the activity of their downstream targets including ribosomal protein S6.
&lt;/Description&gt;

&lt;HGNC&gt;
MTOR
RPTOR
MLST8
&lt;/HGNC&gt;

&lt;Uniprot&gt;
P42345 (MTOR_HUMAN)
Q8N122 (RPTOR_HUMAN)
Q9BVC4 (LST8_HUMAN)
&lt;/Uniprot&gt;

&lt;Observation&gt;
Reported to be active in unperturbed AGS cells in 1 publication (PMID 22421143) and inactive in 1 publication (22907434).
&lt;/Observation&gt;</comment>
