          <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q2TAM5"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q01201"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q04864"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23915189"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/20388956"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/21245990"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/20963626"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/19020743"/>
          <link xlink:href=""/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>&lt;Description&gt;
The node NFkB collapses different members of the Rel/NFkB family, known to regulate the expression of genes that participate in immune, apoptotic and oncogenic processes. 
These include NFkB1, NFkB2, RelA, RelB and  c-Rel. 
NFkB is predominantly localized in the cytoplasm as a complex with inhibitory IkB proteins and is released and translocated to the nucleus after phosphorylation of IkB. 
&lt;/Description&gt;

&lt;HGNC&gt;
RELA
RELB
REL
NFKB1
NFKB2
&lt;/HGNC&gt;

