          <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q15418"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>&lt;Description&gt;
Serine/threonine-protein kinase that acts downstream of ERK (MAPK1/ERK2 and MAPK3/ERK1) signaling and mediates mitogenic and stress-induced activation of the transcription factors CREB1, ETV1/ER81 and NR4A1/NUR77, regulates translation through RPS6 and EIF4B phosphorylation, and mediates cellular proliferation, survival, and differentiation by modulating mTOR signaling and repressing pro-apoptotic function of BAD and DAPK1.
&lt;/Description&gt;

&lt;HGNC&gt;
&lt;/HGNC&gt;

&lt;Uniprot&gt;
P51812 (KS6A3_HUMAN)
Q15349 (KS6A2_HUMAN)
Q15418 (KS6A1_HUMAN)
&lt;/Uniprot&gt;

&lt;Observation&gt;
RPS6KA3 known to contain mutations in AGS.
RPS6KA1 and RPS6KA2 no known mutations in AGS.
RPS6KA1, RPS6KA2, RPS6KA3 expressed in AGS.
&lt;/Observation&gt;</comment>
