          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/12808021"/>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.pubmed.com/pubmed/20584780"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>&lt;Description&gt;
MMP-2, MMP-7 and MMP-9 can cleave cell surface pro-HB-EGF and liberate the soluble active growth factor (PMID 16266693)
&lt;/Description&gt;

&lt;HGNC&gt;
MMP2
MMP7
MMP9
&lt;/HGNC&gt;

&lt;Uniprot&gt;
P08253 (MMP2_HUMAN)
P09237 (MMP7_HUMAN)
P14780 (MMP9_HUMAN)
&lt;/Uniprot&gt;

&lt;Observation&gt;
Not expressed in AGS.
No known mutations in AGS.
Reported to be active in unperturbed AGS cells in 10 publications (PMID 20963626, 20840540, 20651362, 23153558, 20498032, 18347140, 20498032, 20963626, 20651362, 20498032) and inactive in 3 publications (PMID 12808021, 20584780, 20840540)
&lt;/Observation&gt;</comment>
